channel.title: Connecting?
channel.description: Hey. So I recently put my server online, and I got no-ip running, and I portforwarded with uTorrent, and I even used the runelocus server status checker and it says my server is online, but when I download the client to my laptop(which im using right now), it says I cant connect. Im able to connect on the computer im hosting on, but nothing else. Not even the other owner of my server can connect.. any help? Im able to use team viewer. Just say if you want to use my laptop or my hosting comp. THANKS!

item.title: Connecting?
item.dc:creator: @CookieScape CookieScape
item.description:
@CookieScape wrote:

What is your IP set to in your gui.java? You have to set it to your no-ip IP and then compile.

Search for serverip in gui.java client sided. If it is 127.0.0.1 or 0.0.0.0 change it to your no-ip
